{"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Linter.HashCommandLinter","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Lean.Elab.Command","Lean.Linter.Util","Batteries.Lean.HashSet"],"declarations":[{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.lean#L70-L83","name":"Mathlib.Linter.HashCommandLinter.hashCommandLinter","line":70,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.html#Mathlib.Linter.HashCommandLinter.hashCommandLinter","doc":"Checks that no command beginning with `#` is present in 'Mathlib',\nexcept for the ones in `allowed_commands`.\n\nIf `warningAsError` is `true`, then the linter logs an info (rather than a warning).\nThis means that CI will eventually fail on `#`-commands, but does not stop it from continuing.\n\nHowever, in order to avoid local clutter, when `warningAsError` is `false`, the linter\nlogs a warning only for the `#`-commands that do not already emit a message. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.html#Mathlib.Linter.HashCommandLinter.hashCommandLinter\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">HashCommandLinter</span>.<span class=\"name\">hashCommandLinter</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.Linter\">Lean.Linter</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.lean#L41-L41","name":"Mathlib.Linter.HashCommandLinter.getLinterHash","line":41,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.html#Mathlib.Linter.HashCommandLinter.getLinterHash","doc":"Gets the value of the `linter.hashCommand` option. "},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.html#Mathlib.Linter.HashCommandLinter.getLinterHash\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">HashCommandLinter</span>.<span class=\"name\">getLinterHash</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(o : <a href=\"./Lean/Data/Options.html#Lean.Options\">Lean.Options</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/b5eba595428809e96f3ed113bc7ba776c5f801ac/Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.lean#L26-L34","name":"Mathlib.Linter.linter.hashCommand","line":26,"kind":"opaque","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.html#Mathlib.Linter.linter.hashCommand","doc":"The linter emits a warning on any command beginning with `#` that itself emits no message.\nFor example, `#guard true` and `#check_tactic True ~> True by skip` trigger a message.\nThere is a list of silent `#`-command that are allowed.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Linter/HashCommandLinter.html#Mathlib.Linter.linter.hashCommand\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">linter</span>.<span class=\"name\">hashCommand</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Data/Options.html#Lean.Option\">Lean.Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></div></div>"}]}